  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="slabel">How your code works</div>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">01</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <strong>10 seconds to sign up</strong>
          <p>Name, handle, platform, email. No payment, no commitment, no catch.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">02</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <strong>You get a unique referral link</strong>
          <p>Yours only: <span class="ref-url">streamstack.co.nz?ref=vanessa</span></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">03</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <strong>Share wherever your community lives</strong>
          <p>Bio, stories, posts, podcast, newsletter. Go wild.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">04</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <strong>Every Kiwi through your link scores a point</strong>
          <p>Each verified NZ signup updates your rank on the live leaderboard instantly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="slabel">The rules</div>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step"><div class="step-bullet">&bull;</div><div class="step-body"><strong>I run this. My call is final.</strong><p>Rules don't change once the competition opens. No debate.</p></div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="step-bullet">&bull;</div><div class="step-body"><strong>NZ signups only.</strong><p>Only verified New Zealand emails count toward your score.</p></div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="step-bullet">&bull;</div><div class="step-body"><strong>Fakes get wiped.</strong><p>Suspicious or duplicate signups are removed without warning.</p></div></div>
